headline: Give Kids A Smile Program Celebrates 23rd Year of Providing Free Oral Health Care Services to Underserved Children
summary: CHICAGO, February 10, 2025--The American Dental Association Foundation (ADA Foundation) is celebrating the 23rd year of its Give Kids A Smile® (GKAS) program, which officially launched on Friday, February 7, at the 2025 national kick-off event at Meharry Medical College School of Dentistry. Since its national launch in 2003, GKAS volunteers have provided free oral health education and services to more than 9.5 million underserved children in the U.S.
